  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money appear legitimate by disguising its true source. This is typically done through complex financial transactions and schemes. In China, the government has established a comprehensive legal framework to combat money laundering. The Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China, along with other relevant regulations and measures, clearly defines money laundering as a criminal offense and outlines stringent measures for its prevention, investigation, and punishment. The Chinese government is committed to maintaining financial security and order, and it actively participates in international cooperation to combat money laundering and related crimes.",
